        <h2 id="Recipe1">Student's dinner</h2>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 2 hours</li>
            <li>Serves: 3 people</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                    <th>preparing time</th>
                </tr>
                
            </thead>
            <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>onion</td>
                <td>200 g  </td>
                <td> 15 mins</td>
                
             </tr>

                <tr>
                <td>carrot</td>
                <td>100g </td>
                <td> 3 mins</td>
                
             </tr>
                          <tr>
                <td>meat</td>
                <td>1 kg</td>
                <td> 5 mins</td>
                
             </tr>
                          <tr>
                <td>spices</td>
                <td>10 g</td>
                <td> - </td>
                
             </tr>
                          <tr>
                <td>potato</td>
                <td>500 g</td>
                <td> 10 mins</td>
                
             </tr>
                          <tr>
                <td>water</td>
                <td>500 ml</td>
                <td> 0.5h </td>
                
             </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> put onion in the hot pan and wait untill it becomes yellow.
</p>
        <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> add a carrot and wait untill it becomes soft. 
</p>
        <p><strong>Step3 :</strong>add meat for 5 mins
</p>
        <p><strong>Step 4:</strong> add potato and fry for 10 mins 
</p>
        <p><strong>Step 5:</strong> add water and close the pan. Wait 30 mins and then you can eat it. 
</p>

